><br></div><div>GENDERED WORK and DIY MAKING</div><div>JULIA BRYAN-WILSON in conversation with JON RAYMOND</div><div>Friday, April 20, 2018</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>SEASON #4—CHANTAL AKERMAN</div><div><br></div><div>ERRANT SOUL: FROM EAST TO WEST AND IN-BETWEEN: LUIS CROQUER and MARAT GRINBERG</div><div>October 28, 2016</div><div><br></div><div>CHANTAL AKERMAN: LA PASSION DE L\'INTIME / AN INTIMATE PASSION: BERENICE REYNAUD</div><div>November 20, 2016</div><div><br></div><div>STUDIO VISIT: 90.3 FM PORTLAND: THE MUSIC IN THE FILMS OF CHANTAL AKERMAN: SANDRA PERCIVAL and DR. ABIGAIL SUSIK</div><div>April 30, 2017</div><div><br></div><div>THE WIND CROSSES THE BROWN LAND, UNHEARD: LAURA FRIED and KYSS JEAN-MARY</div><div>May 14, 2017</div><div><br></div><div>MY MOTHER LAUGHS (MA MERE RIT): ACTOR, GRACE CARTER with PAIGE MCKINNEY and RON MASON GASSAWAY</div><div>May 18, 2017</div><div><br></div><div>CHANTAL? DIALOGUE BETWEEN A MOVIE, A CELLO AND A TEXT SONIA WIEDER-ATHERTON</div><div>May 1 and 2, 2018</div><div>*Traveled to REDCAT, Los Angeles; and NW Film Forum, Seattle</div><div><br></div><div>PERFORMANCE, VOICE AND MUSIC IN THE WORK OF CHANTAL AKERMAN: SANDRA PERCIVAL and SONIA WIEDER-ATHERTON</div><div>May 2, 2018</div><div><br></div><div>SEASON #3—STAN DOUGLAS</div><div><br></div><div>RECONTEXTUALIZATION + RONIN: AN APPROACH TO THE WESTERN IN STAN DOUGLAS\'S FILMS: MARK BERRETTINI</div><div>September 17, 2015</div><div><br></div><div>SCREENING OF STAN DOUGLAS FILM, \"KLATSSASIN\" (2006)</div><div>September 17, 2015</div><div><br></div><div>THE UNCANNY AND OTHER SWEET NOTHINGS: JAN MIESZKOWSKI and SANDRA PERCIVAL</div><div>September 24, 2015</div><div><br></div><div>SCREENING OF SAMUEL BECKETT\'S \"NOT, I\" (1972) &amp; STAN DOUGLAS\'S \"MIME, DEUX DEVISES\" (1983)</div><div>February 24, 2015</div><div><br></div><div>SCREENING OF BECKETT\'S \"FILM\" (1963) &amp; STAN DOUGLAS\'S \"VIDEO\" (2007)&nbsp;</div><div>February 24, 2015</div><div><br></div><div>MINOR WHITE: 1857 PROJECT</div><div>June 7 – August 29, 2015</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>SEASON #2—ANTHONY MCCALL</div><div><br></div><div>PICTURE YOURSELF, A MOTE: KRIS COHEN and ABIGAIL SUSIK&nbsp;</div><div>February 7, 2015</div><div><br></div><div>ARGUMENT: THOMAS BEARD February 21, 2015</div><div><br></div><div>THE ARTIST, THE ART OF FILM AND THE INSTITUTION: RUDOLF FRIELING&nbsp;</div><div>February 21, 2015</div><div><br></div><div>IN THE SPIRIT OF JEAN DUPUY\'S 1974 SOUP &amp; TART: Pistou soup, bread and apple tarts served to 100 guests followed by 40 Portland artists, writers and musicians each performing two-minute pieces for what Dupuy called the \"performance menu.\"</div><div>February 28, 2015</div><div><br></div><div>LAURA HEIT: 1857 PROJECT</div><div>October 19, 2014 – February 21, 2015</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>SEASON #1—JOSIAH MCELHENY</div><div><br></div><div>PASSAGE WORK: PAUL SCHEERBART, WALTER BENJAMIN &amp; JOSIAH MCELHENY\'S \"LIGHT CLUB\" FILMS: ROBERT SITTON and JOHN URANG</div><div>October 19, 2013</div><div><br></div><div>MODERNISM\'S UTOPIAS &amp; ARTISTS AS AGENTS: JOYCE CHENG and MAREK WIECZOREK</div><div>October 26, 2013</div><div><br></div><div>THE ABSTRACT BODY &amp; FASHION: ANN HAMILTON and JESSICA BURSTEIN</div><div>November 2, 2013</div><div><br></div><div>SCREENING OF OSKAR SCHLEMMER\'S \"TRIADIC BALLET\" (1922)</div><div>November 2, 2013</div><div><br></div><div>INSIDER/OUTLIERS: LYNNE COOKE with JOSIAH MCELHENY, University of Oregon, Eugene</div><div>November 15, 2013</div><div><br></div><div>INTERIORS: JOSIAH MCELHENY and LYNNE COOKE</div><div>November 16, 2013</div><div><br></div><div>\"THE LIGHT CLUB\' AT THE LUMBER ROOM: ALISON COBB, JEN COLEMAN, PAUL MAZIER, JOHN SHIPLEY and MARY SUTTON This celebration of a fictional event enacts McElheny\'s own theatrical gathering for the \"Centenary of the Light Club of Batavia.\" In Paul Scheerbart\'s novella, \"The Light Club of Batavia: A Ladies Novelette,\" the fabulous creation of the light spa at the bottom of a mineshaft is noted just so: \"The five gathered again in Batavia in July 1910. And Mr. Hartung confirmed that everything was bright.\"</div><div>December 7, 2013</div>',_binary '\r\n																								\r\n																								\r\n																								\r\n																								\r\n																								\r\n																								\r\n																								\r\n																								'),(342,0,'2021-04-23 00:00:04','2021-04-23 00:01:53',NULL,'Seasons',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'342',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(343,1,'2021-05-10 12:02:21','2021-05-10 12:02:21',30,'Images',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'images',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
